The paper deals with the problem of finding a polynomial kernel for the $\mathcal{H}$-free Edge Deletion problem, which is a graph problem. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Among these categories, cs.DS and cs.DM are the most likely as they deal with graph algorithms and combinatorial optimization. cs.CC and cs.CG are also likely as they deal with computational complexity and graph-related problems. cs.GT is less likely as it deals with game theory, which is not directly related to the problem at hand.
